text: Welcome to this cozy, rustic retreat amongst the trees. Just 10 minutes from downtown Blaine, this nearly 5-acre property at the end of a quiet private road offers unmatched privacy. Enjoy the covered porch, your own pond, and a seasonal creek. The main floor has a primary bedroom, with two more bedrooms upstairs. The 1100 SF walk-in basement offers storage and leisure space, plus a framed room for an office and an unfinished bathroom. The 28'x32' shop stores your tools, including the John Deere riding mower and its accessory trailer that convey with the home. Multiple fenced areas ensure your pets stay safe. Recent upgrades: new Hardie siding (2023), new septic system (2015), and a newer roof.

A rare opportunity to own a 1.05-acre parcel of vacant land in a serene and remote east side of Point Roberts, offered at an exceptional value! This beautiful property offers stunning ocean views and has available water hook-up and electricity, making it ideal for those looking to build a dream home with added privacy. The land features some beautiful old-growth trees, providing a serene and natural setting. In addition, the location is conveniently located just 30-45 minutes away from YVR (Vancouver International Airport). Don't miss this exceptional opportunity!

Charming single-story 3-bedroom, 1.75-bath home in Richmond Park, Birch Bay, offered for the first time by its original owner. This well-maintained home features a primary bedroom with an en suite bath and walk-in closet, new vinyl plank flooring, and a separate laundry room between the house and attached 2-car garage. The spacious yard backs onto neighborhood greenspace and includes full decks, a covered porch, patio, hot tub hookups, and a dog run. RV parking with hookups, public water/sewer, and natural gas. Close to Birch Bays beaches, dining, and outdoor activities. Move-in ready!

Discover this charming, well-kept single-level home, set on a generous lot in a prime mid-county location. Bright, clean, and move-in ready, this 3-bedroom residence is filled with thoughtful details, from light filled rooms, dual closets in the primary bedroom, to the updated bathroom, and cozy gas fireplace in the family room. Functional and attractive, the kitchen features modern-classic cabinetry and granite counters, along with French doors that open to a Trex deck, creating a seamless connection to the private, fully fenced yardperfect for relaxation or play. With ample parking and a location on a quiet dead-end street, just minutes from downtown Lynden, this home offers the ideal lifestyle mix to put down your roots.

This 4BD, 2.5BA property is your cozy PNW dream come true! In the spacious living room, youll find vaulted ceilings, fireplace, and a charming crescent window for tons of natural light. Perfect for entertaining, youll love the finished lower level & the open concept kitchen with wood floors and plenty of cabinet storage. Your large primary suite is the star of the show with attached bath ft. a separate shower & huge tub. Step out onto the back deck to enjoy the peaceful, private feel of this property perfect for morning coffee or evening gatherings. With a brand-new roof and hot water heater, + access to all Sudden Valley amenities, this home is turn-key and ready to become your haven in the woods.

This stunning Glacier A-frame is the ultimate retreat for outdoor enthusiasts & cozy cabin lovers alike. Fully updated & meticulously maintained, the cabin boasts a welcoming living space with a charming fireplace, perfect for relaxing after a day of skiing, hiking, or exploring the nearby trails. A modern kitchen with stainless steel appliances & eating area. 3 spacious bedrooms offers tranquil views. On the back deck where youll find yourself immersed in serene forest surroundings. The cabin features a new roof, windows, and siding, ensuring long-term durability and peace of mind. Perfect for a full-time residence, a weekend getaway, or a high-demand vacation rental! Truly a perfect blend of rustic charm and modern convenience!

Welcome to this stunning 3-bed, 2-bath, 1678 sq ft single-level home on 3/4 acre of private, level land in the heart of the county. Enjoy a detached 1200 sq ft shop, perfect for projects or storage. The serene grounds boast mature landscaping, spacious driveway, new front porch, and rear deck w/ a hot tub for ultimate relaxation. Inside, find a bright, open living area, dining off the kitchen, roomy bedrooms, and easy-care LVP flooring. Cozy up by the gas or wood fireplaces. The primary bedroom features an ensuite bath, and the kitchen w/ a 5-burner gas stove. Recent updates include roofing & siding on the house & shop, argon front windows, and interior & exterior paint. Centrally located with easy access to amenities and is move-in ready.

Impeccably cared for and move-in ready 3bed 2bath home reflects true pride of ownership. Recent upgrades include a brand-new roof, fresh interior and exterior paint, energy-efficient LED fixtures, new water heater and generator hookups, all designed for comfort and efficiency. The updated kitchen features modern appliances and sleek countertops, while both bathrooms have been stylishly remodeled with contemporary finishes. Outside, the owners have transformed the backyard into a private retreat with an extended patio, new privacy fence, and pristine landscaping, perfect for relaxing or entertaining. This home offers ample parking for an RV, fifth wheel, or boat. Located just minutes from Blaines beaches, parks, and local amenities.

Development potential in Chuckanut Village! Serene half acre+ on Chuckanut Creek. Capture water views of Chuckanut Bay from a proposed 2 or 3 story/addition. This enchanting property is one of a kind! This cozy 1 bedroom cottage is a successful VRBO/Airbnb extended stay w/over $30k/yr income. Newly installed 3 bed septic system provides an opportunity to expand the footprint of the home & capture water views of North Chuckanut Bay. Buyer to verify. Located on a dead end street, the privacy and quiet is unparalleled in Bellingham. Nearby access to saltwater and the Chuckanut Trail system puts recreation at your back door! Enjoy the tranquility of the Salmon runs in the fall & feel like you have it all to yourself. Sold as-is.

Sweet little home, cabin, hide-a-way, weekend retreat, rental, you name it - this will do it. Salt water view from the front deck and a fully fenced and private rear deck and firepit area. Well maintained 720 sf, 2 bedroom home in good shape now with potential to be something really special. The home and improvements only sit on 1/2 the land, the rest is level grassy area that will be great for all the games, gatherings, gardening, wiffleball or ??. Located on a quiet stretch 1/2 block off the beach in the Neptune Beach community this will provide years of memories and be a solid addition to any real estate portfolio.

Charming Craftsman style home with ADU perched on top of Sehome Hill, backing to the Arboretum. This quaint 2 bed/1 bath home features brand new flooring on main level & recently refinished hardwood floors in bedrooms. Daylight unfinished basement plumbed for a full bath offers endless potential. Enjoy morning coffees on the front porch while taking in the beautiful view. Fully fenced private backyard leads to a spacious 550sq.ft. ADU 1bd/1bth perfect for generating additional rental income w/additional parking in back. A trail right outside your backyard takes you directly into the arboretum to campus, making this the ideal location for those who love easy access to nature & downtown Bellingham. Exterior recently painted for a fresh look.

Development potential in Chuckanut Village! Serene half acre+ on Chuckanut Creek. Capture water views of Chuckanut Bay from a proposed 2 or 3 story/addition. This enchanting property is one of a kind! This cozy 1 bedroom cottage is a successful VRBO/Airbnb extended stay w/over $30k/yr income. Newly installed 3 bed septic system provides an opportunity to expand the footprint of the home & capture water views of North Chuckanut Bay. Buyer to verify. Located on a dead end street, the privacy and quiet is unparalleled in Bellingham. Nearby access to saltwater and the Chuckanut Trail system puts recreation at your back door! Enjoy the tranquility of the Salmon runs in the fall & feel like you have it all to yourself. Sold as-is.

Updated 3 bed 2.5 bath home on a quiet cul-de-sac in Tweed Twenty/Silver Beach neighborhood. This open-concept home features a spacious, beautifully renovated kitchen with new appliances, and gorgeous hardwood floors throughout the first floor. Primary bedroom on the main level. Brand new composite deck and a level and fenced backyard with raised beds. Room for RV or boat parking. Lake Whatcom is around the corner, as well as Northridge Park (trail and playground). Or, hop on the Railroad Trail to Whatcom Falls Park or even downtown. A sweet home in a magical little area of Bellingham!

Seamlessly blending modern updates w/classic Craftsman charm, this remodeled home sits in the heart of Bellingham.A 4 bed/1.75-bath gem offering 1, 736 sq ft of thoughtfully updated living space w/eco-friendly features throughout.Equipped w/solar panels, heat pump water heater, a pro series induction stove, & new insulation in both the attic & crawl space, this home boasts no electric bill & avg gas bill of $35/month! Plus an electric car charger to boot!Great walkability to downtown & the waterfront, making it easy to explore local shops, dining, & outdoor activities.Plenty of parking options w/a 1-car garage, long driveway, & street parking, plus alley access to the beautifully landscaped backyard w/raised flower beds & mature fruit trees.
nearby_schools: Bellingham Public Schools, Northwest Educational Service District 189

text: Nicely treed lot tucked away on a quiet and private cul-de-sac in the Dogwood Park subdivision. Beautiful Park like setting with a mix of Douglas Fir, Western Red Cedar and ferns where you can build that cottage or home that you've always wanted. Great soils for septic and it has a WATER METER! Centrally located with a short walk to the border and transit system to take you into the city. No Mobiles Allowed in this subdivision. Be sure to check out link to online video tour.

You'll just love the grand sweeping views of the Bay and the surrounding mountains, with only footsteps to the beach. This Beautifully updated home features NEW kitchen cabinets and countertops, stainless steel appliances, flooring, paint, carpet, lighting, windows, doors, roof, siding, and etc. With sweeping views from the primary bedroom, as well as from your kitchen, living room and dining area, you just love this home. With tons of natural light throughout, and large covered decks for entertaining, this home is an absolute must see!

With breathtaking, unobstructed views of the valley and mountains and high-end finishes throughout, this home perfectly blends luxury and nature. It lives like a single-level home, with the added bonus of a daylight basement designed for entertaining. The main floor showcases an open-concept layout and a chefs kitchen featuring a massive center island, ideal for cooking and gathering. The living area seamlessly extends to a covered deck, offering stunning views and an exceptional indoor-outdoor living experience. High-end finishes continue throughout the home, along with expansive storage spaces to meet every need. Whether hosting guests or soaking in the peaceful views, this property is a true gem offering both luxury and functionality.

Come home to this private & functional property that has it all: stunning Mt. Baker views, 4.9 acres, ADU, 2 large shops, solar power and more! The 2, 507 sqft single-level home features vaulted ceilings, A/C and a front row seat to every Mt. Baker sunrise & sunset. The spacious primary bedroom with en suite features a walk-in closet, jetted tub & door to backyard. The main living area is light & bright with tall windows and skylights. ADU is form & function: 900sqft 2 bed apartment w/ large dedicated deck, 4 garage bays including a dedicated RV bay. Last but not least, a standalone 1, 000sqft shop with office and lift. Enjoy the peace and quiet of your own private 5 acre retreat at the end of a paved private road. Must see in person!

Nestled in a quiet neighborhood on a large lot close to town, this cheerful home offers convenience and comfort. Main floor living. Spacious kitchen w/breakfast bar + oversized pantry. Sliding doors in the dining area open to a fenced side yard. Private hallway off the living room leads to a cozy primary bedroom (with new carpet) and a full bath. Heated office/sunroom is filled with natural light, perfect for a home office or craft room. Newly carpeted upper level includes bedroom + bonus space. Large lot with mature landscaping and room for gardening and entertaining! Detached garage, shed, additional RV/vehicle parking. Never flooded in 30+ years of ownership. Easy access to local amenities and Canadian border - a truly delightful home!

An amazing location and a huge price reduction combine to make this 3 bedroom 2 bath county home on 14 acres something you don't want to miss. Recently refurbished, this home shines! Big mountain and valleys views with privacy at the very end of your long, new $80, 000 driveway means privacy to enjoy your custom home. Two decks watch the views, more views from your chef's style kitchen and there's even a view from the master bath and family room. Vaulted ceilings provide a roomy feel, and one level living is very convenient. Oversized 3 car garage...and a huge crawlspace for future uses. Lots of timber on site and a big shop too. Seller is motivated!

The Clover by MainVue Homes at Horizon is a rambler home design with all-season allure. Enter past the chic front door and find two secondary bedrooms and a Hall Bathroom. The Gourmet Kitchen features 3cm Quartz Counters, Stainless Steel appliances and a Grand Butlers Pantry. The Signature Outdoor Room is capped in Trex Composite Decking and connects the Great Room and Dining room, illuminated by a luxurious nine bulb Dining room chandelier. The Grand Suite awaits off these main living areas and features an expansive walk-in dressing room, designer free-standing tub and frameless walk-in shower. Customer registration policy: Buyers Broker to visit or be registered on Buyers 1st visit for full Commission is reduced.

Welcome to Whispering Meadows! This spacious 3-bedroom, 1.75-bath home boasts all the latest trendy fixtures. The main living area is highlighted by vaulted ceilings that create an open & bright atmosphere. The kitchen is a showstopper with its modern design, featuring chic pendant lighting over the island, soft-close cabinets, quartz countertops, & SS appliances. The primary bedroom offers a large walk-in closet, a double vanity, & a walk-in shower. The home also has a huge private backyard perfect for entertaining. Ductless mini-splits to keep you comfortable year-round. Plus, rest easy knowing this house is not in a flood zone. This beautifully designed rambler is exactly what you've been searching for.

INVESTOR/ FIRST TIME HOME BUYER ALERT! Perfect duplex, each with two bedrooms 1 full bath, open floor plan with kitchen, dining area, and spacious living rooms. Separate laundry room and ample closet space. Updated flooring, and fixtures. each has its own covered parking with outdoor storage and plenty more parking spots in front. Huge shared, fenced backyard with planter boxes and back alley! All this is centrally located steps from Barkley Village on a quiet street. Hurry this won't last long

Whether youre looking for a serene retreat or a place to raise animals, this hobby farm on a stunning 4.77-acres has much to offer! This charming 3BR/2BA rambler home offers the perfect blend of comfort and nature. Enjoy easy, one-level living w/ a well-cared-for interior, including hardwood & tile floors throughout, spacious kitchen w/ eating bar & dining room. Large bay windows overlooks woods & creek. Step outside to find a spacious paddock, ideal for horses or other animals, plus a beautiful meadow for grazing. Explore the wooded lands that provide privacy and a peaceful setting, and listen to the gentle sound of the nearby creek. Oversized 2-car garage + shop space, outbuildings & hot tub nestled in the woods makes a serene retreat.

This beautifully maintained, single-owner 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom rambler has been lovingly cared for since its construction. The open floor plan offers vaulted ceilings and hardwood floors, while the modern kitchen is equipped with granite countertops, cherry cabinets, stainless steel appliances, and a spacious walk-in pantry. The primary bedroom includes a walk-in closet and an ensuite bathroom with a double-sink vanity and walk-in shower. Enjoy the warmth of the gas fireplace or unwind in the fully fenced backyard. Additional highlights include 9' ceilings, new exterior paint (2024), and a 2-car garage with finished walls, fresh paint and trim. Near I-5, shopping, restaurants, medical facilities, walking trails and more. Move in ready!
nearby_schools: Bellingham Public Schools, Northwest Educational Service District 189

text: Nestled in a serene and private Geneva neighborhood, this home sits on an oversized, tranquil third-acre lot. Beautifully maintained for 40 plus yrs by the same family, this one-level home features a spacious, updated kitchen open to the living areas, that is perfect for entertaining. Expansive windows and sliders invite natural light and provide views of the beautifuly landscaped and very private fully fenced, flat yard that is framed by towering evergreens. Enjoy abundant storage throughout, with more in an oversized 2-car attached garage. Situated in a peaceful, ZERO-traffic location, youre just two blocks from Lake Whatcom and moments from Galbraith Mountain trails and three picturesque city parks. Two backyard sheds included.

Build your dream home on 5 acres and enjoy the privacy and peacefulness the mountains provide. This build site is ready to go! Approved 4 bedroom septic design, shared well installed with pump and underground pump house and pressure tanks, power on site complete with transformer and temp power meter approved by PSE. Current owners have a site plan approved by Whatcom County. This is an opportunity you don't want to pass up!

Discover unparalleled waterfront living in this 2-bedroom, 2-bath condo w/ unobstructed views. The open-concept main floor is bathed in natural light, w/ expansive windows and high ceilings. Entertain on the large private patio or enjoy the beach fire pit just steps from your door. The oversized primary bedroom offers the soothing sound of waves and stunning bay and mountain views from every window. Moor your boat out back for easy crabbing trips. With 3 yr new flooring, carpet, SS appliances, a newer hot water tank, excellent established HOA with low dues, this rare gem!

Escape to your very own sanctuary in the woods, just mins away from Barkley Village & DT BHAM. This stunning home has endless features to offer. The kitchen has a huge multi level island & a walk-in pantry. Large vaulted ceilings & exposed wood beams in the living room & kitchen. Beautifully crafted trim work adds a touch of elegance throughout the home. Continue on the main floor & you'll find an office, 1/2 bath, utility room, & the primary bedroom. Primary bed boasts an amazing tiled shower. Descend the beautifully tiled stairs to the large flex space, perfect for any need. You'll also find 2 additional bedrooms, each with en suite bathrooms & walk-in closets. Oversized 3 car garage. New A/C installed just in time for the warm months.

This beautiful top floor unit features stainless appliances, hard surface countertops and a great open floor plan. Large common areas allow for larger group gatherings. Lots of great amenities, close to restaurants and just 5 minutes from downtown Lynden!

Welcome to this charming rambler in Glenhaven offering single-story living with 3 bedrooms and 1 bath. Set on a spacious, fully fenced double lot, this home features cozy electric heating throughout, complemented by a wood stove in the living room for added warmth. The property boasts a massive 1200 sq ft shop with 12' ceilings, fully insulated and ready for electrical installation, making it a versatile space for projects or storage. Enjoy the many amenities, including a park, a clubhouse, a pool, scenic trails, and 3 boat launches all within walking distance. Conveniently located with easy access to I-5 for effortless commuting.

Nestled between Lake Whatcom & the Puget Sound, w/ views over downtown Bellingham & the Bay lies this Barkley home ready for your personal touch. Fresh interior paint, new carpet, high ceilings, & refinished oak floors create a warm, inviting atmosphere. Its open layout, gas range, & large bar are perfect for hosting, while easy-care mature landscaping adds charm. With a main-floor bed & bath, it's ideal for any stage of life. Enjoy the upstairs primary bedroom's en-suite bath, walk-in closet, & cozy fireplace, ft. a west facing rooftop deck perfect for morning coffee & evening sunsets. A short walk from Barkley's shops, restaurants, & cinema, as well as Northridge Park & Bellingham trails, this home offers convenience & comfort year-round.
